<h3><b>EQUIPPING MAGIC ITEMS</b></h3>
<p>
  Magic items require some of the bearer's Essence, or their life energy, in
  order to function. By default, an adventurer has 100 Essence Points. An
  adventurer cannot equip items whose sum Essence cost exceeds this limit.
</p>
<p>
  For example, an adventurer could equip two items that each cost 30 Essence,
  and one that costs 40. An adventurer could not equip three items that each
  cost 40 Essence, as this would exceed 100 total Essence.
</p>
<h3><b>ITEMS STRENGTH</b></h3>
<p>
  Magic items range in power from convenient tools to artifacts that could
  rewrite world events. When designing your own magic items, as you try to
  determine your item's Essence cost, use this table as a reference.
</p>
<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
