<h2>
  <b>ARMOR</b>
</h2>
<h3>
  <b>ACIDWALKER'S ARMOR</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Medium, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Scale Mail</p>
<p>
  The black scales of this scale mail armor appear to be made of chitin. You
  gain Immune Corrosive.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>CHAMELEON HIDE</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Light, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Hide Armor</p>
<p>
  This set of stitched hide armor changes color to match the wearer's
  environment. You gain +10 to DEX/Sneaking checks while remaining still.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>DIVING SUIT</b>
</h3>
<p>
  <em>Armor, Heavy, Unwieldy, Uncommon, Essence 15</em>
</p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Banded Mail</p>
<p>
  This suit of specialized mail covers a medium humanoid's entire body. It has 1
  charge, which it regains 1 hour before dawn each day. You can activate the
  Diving Suit by spending the charge. You gain a swim speed equal to your
  walking speed and gain the ability to breathe underwater for 1 hour.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>FLAMEWALKER'S ARMOR</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Medium, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Scale Mail</p>
<p>
  The dark red scales of this scale mail armor appear to be made of chitin. You
  gain Immune Fire.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>GUARDIAN'S SHIELD</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Shield, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Heater Shield</p>
<p>
  This steel heater shield is edged in silver. You may spend 1 Reactive AP when
  an ally within 5 ft of you is attacked. Grant them +1 AR vs that attack. This
  bonus increases to +3 AR if used against a ranged weapon attack. You can use
  this feature once per round, resetting at the start of each of your turns.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>ICEWALKER'S ARMOR</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Medium, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Scale Mail</p>
<p>
  The icy white scales of this scale mail armor appear to be made of chitin. You
  gain Immune Cold.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>IRON MAIDEN'S PLATE</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Heavy, Unwieldy, Epic, Essence 30</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Plate (Full)</p>
<p>
  This suit of plate mail is made from dull, rusted iron and its interior is
  lined with blunted spikes. The helmet is molded into the visage of a screaming
  woman. You may activate the armor and immediately take 1d8 sharp damage. Until
  the start of your next turn, you gain +6 to attack and damage rolls with STR
  melee weapons and gain Immune Charmed, Demoralized, Enthralled, Frightened,
  and Shaken.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>LEAFDANCER'S CUIRASS</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Light, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Cuirass (Leather)</p>
<p>
  This cuirass is made of stitched green leaves. This armor has 1 charge,
  regaining its charge daily at dawn. You may expend the charge and spend 10
  minutes in direct sunlight to regain 1d8 HP. Doing so also provides
  nourishment equivalent to a standard meal.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>LUCKY CUTOFF VEST</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Light, Common, Essence 10</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p><em> </em></p>
<p><b>Base: </b>Gambeson</p>
<p>
  While wearing the Lucky Cutoff Vest, you can give yourself +5 to REF when your
  REF is attacked until the beginning of your next turn. This extra REF is free
  the first time you do it, and 2 Reactive AP on concurrent uses. You regain
  your free use upon Taking a Rest.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>MIRROR SHIELD</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Shield, Rare, Essence 25</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base:</b> Heater Shield</p>
<p>
  This round shield has a perfectly mirrored silver surface. It has 3 charges,
  and regains 1 charge every dawn. You may spend 1 charge and 2 Reactive AP
  after being hit by a ranged attack that targets no other creatures. Any damage
  dealt from the attack is instead dealt back to the attacker. You can use this
  feature once per round, resetting at the start of each of your turns.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>PHALANX TOWER SHIELD</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Shield, Uncommon, Essence 25</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Tower Shield</p>
<p>
  This wooden tower shield is edged in bronze and has a single bronze cap at its
  center. The shield has 2 charges, and regains both charges at dawn each day.
  You may activate the Phalanx Tower Shield to create a 20 ft radius magical
  zone centered on where this feature was activated (it does not move with you).
  Creatures may pass freely into and out of the zone. Any creature inside the
  zone is immune to nonmagical ranged attacks that originate outside the zone.
  This zone lasts for 1 minute.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>ROBES OF THE ARCHMAGE</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Light, Epic, Essence 35</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Robes (Elemental)</p>
<p>
  This magnificently crafted black silk robe is fringed in gold thread and is
  stitched with the motif of a thousand stars. You gain Resist Elemental 8.
  Spells cost 2 fewer AP (min 1) for you to cast.
</p>
<br />
<p>You may spend 6 AP to regain ½ your SP. (1/Rest)</p>
<h3>
  <b>SECOND SKIN</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Light, Rare, Essence 20</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base:</b> Hide Armor</p>
<p>
  This set of stitched hide armor appears to be made from various human skins.
  After being equipped, the armor molds with the wearer's skin and cannot be
  removed except with Lesser Restoration or equivalent magic. While equipped,
  you gain Immune Petrified and Immune Paralyzed, and you cannot have your form
  changed – willingly or otherwise – by magic such as Polymorph.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>SHIELD OF THORNS</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Shield, Rare, Essence 20</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Buckler</p>
<p>
  This round iron buckler is covered in twisting metal thorns. You can make a 0
  Reactive AP special attack immediately after a creature makes a melee attack
  against you. The special attack is +DEX vs REF. <b>Hit: </b>1d6 sharp and the
  target gains Bleeding (1). You can use this feature once per round, resetting
  at the start of each of your turns.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>SUNBURST SHIELD</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Shield, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base:</b> Heater Shield</p>
<p>
  This round wooden shield is painted with a highly detailed sun motif. The
  Sunburst Shield has 3 charges and regains 1 charge daily at dawn. You may
  spend 1 charge and 2 AP to activate the shield. Make a special attack: +CHA vs
  the WILL of all creatures in a 10 ft cone. <b>Hit: </b>Those creatures gain
  the Blinded condition until the end of their next turn.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>SYMBIOTIC MIMIC</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Light, Rare, Essence 20</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Leather Armor</p>
<p>
  This set of plain leather armor is actually a non-hostile mimic in disguise.
  You gain +2 AR and may spend 4 AP to change this armor's base to leather
  armor, scale mail or plate (full). Additionally, you cannot be Surprised.
  However, when you regain HP, you only regain ½ that amount. Unequipping the
  armor requires a successful DC 14 CHA check; on a failure, you cannot attempt
  to remove the armor again for 24 hours. Lesser Restoration or similar magic
  can also remove the armor.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>VOLCANIC PLATE</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Armor, Heavy, Unwieldy, Epic, Essence 30</em></p>
<br />

<p><b>Base: </b>Plate (Full)</p>
<p>
  This suit of field plate is made from pure obsidian and is covered in veins of
  faintly glowing red crystal. You gain Immune Fire but gain Vulnerable Cold 1.
  Additionally, you can activate the Volcanic Plate for 2 AP, which gives off an
  intense heat. This heat causes highly flammable objects that are not being
  worn or carried to catch fire. Any creature that starts its turn within 5 ft
  of you takes 1d6 fire damage while this feature is active. You may deactivate
  the armor for 2 AP.
</p>
<h2>
  <b>ITEMS</b>
</h2>
<h3>
  <b>AMULET OF THIRST</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Necklace, Common, Essence 10</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  This simple amulet is made from a clear crystal wrapped in gold on a golden
  chain. The amulet has 1 charge and regains its charge at dawn each day. After
  spending 1 hour submerged in a potion, this amulet stores that potion's effect
  as the crystal takes on that potion's color. This expends the amulet's charge.
  The potion then becomes mundane liquid. You may activate the amulet for 1 AP
  and immediately gain the stored effect as if you had consumed the potion
  yourself. After using this feature, the amulet's crystal returns to its
  original clear state and no longer has any potion effects.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>BOOK OF SECRETS</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Book, Rare, Essence 35</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  This book is bound in an unidentifiable leather dyed a dark blue and is edged
  in elegant gold leaf. The book has 6 charges, and regains 1d4 charges at dawn
  each day. If examined, the pages inside are blank, and if you write in the
  book, it disappears after 1 hour. By spending 1 charge, speaking a command
  word, and saying the name of one humanoid within 10 miles of you, the pages
  within the book begin to fill with information about that target humanoid as
  if written by a personal biographer. Anyone who spends 30 minutes reading this
  book gains a +8 to any INT/History check made to learn information about the
  target humanoid, and gains a +6 to AWR/Intuiting, CHA/Intimidating, and
  CHA/Persuading when interacting with the target humanoid for the next 24
  hours. This writing remains in the book for 1 hour, after which it fades and
  becomes blank once again.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>BOOTS OF THE SWIFTWIND</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Boots, Rare, Essence 20</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  These sheepskin boots are dyed a light grey-blue and have silver capped heels.
  These boots grant you +10 ft walking speed and double your horizontal jump
  distance. Once per day, you can click the heels of these boots together and
  gain a vertical jump height of 20 ft until the end of their next turn.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>BOTTOMLESS BAG</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Container, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  This green-velvet bag is tied with a golden string and can open to a diameter
  of 1 ft. The bag appears empty when examined or turned inside out but anything
  deposited into it disappears into a pocket dimension. By spending 2 AP, you
  can reach into the bag and retrieve something stored within this pocket
  dimension. It can be a random item (determined by the MC) or a specific one.
  The Bottomless Bag can hold up to 500 lbs of items but never weighs more than
  2 lbs when worn. The bottomless bag's pocket dimension contains no breathable
  air. The bag's environment is considered ambient room temperature, and organic
  matter will rot at its normal rate.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>BEASTHEART GAUNTLETS</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Gloves, Rare, Essence 20</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  These leather gauntlets are wrapped in thick brown fur. You gain +1 STR and
  you gain an additional damage die to all your unarmed attacks (e.g. 1d4
  becomes 2d4).
</p>
<h3>
  <b>BRACERS OF CONDUCTION</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Gloves, Rare, Essence 20</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  These silver gauntlets are decorated with lightning bolts of white crystal.
  You gain Resist Lightning 3. Additionally, when you take lightning damage, you
  gain 1 charge for every 3 damage taken, to a maximum of 4 charges. When you
  make a melee or ranged attack, you may spend +1 AP to consume any number of
  charges as part of the attack. If the attack hits, the target takes +1d10
  lightning damage for every charge consumed.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>BREWER'S CASK</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Container, Common, Essence 10</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  This small oaken cask has two silver bands carved with images of grape vines.
  Any mundane item or liquid sealed inside the Brewer's Cask ages 1 year for
  every hour.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>CARRION CLOAK</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Cloak, Rare, Essence 30</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  This cloak appears to be nothing more than tattered, foul-smelling rags
  infested with all manner of insects. The cloak has 1 charge, and regains its
  charge daily at dusk. You may spend 2 AP and 1 charge to summon 1d4
  <b>Swarms of Insects. </b>These swarms appear in unoccupied spaces within 5 ft
  of you and go immediately after you in Initiative. They follow your mental
  commands and last for 10 minutes or until reduced to 0 HP, whereupon they
  dissipate.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>CIRCLET OF MIND SHIELDING</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Helmet, Rare, Essence 30</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  This plain steel circlet has a single ruby set on the forehead. You gain
  Immune Psychic, Charmed, and Enthralled. You are also Immune to any magical
  ability that reads thoughts.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>CIRCLET OF THOUGHT DETECTION</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Helmet, Rare, Essence 20</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  This elegant silver circlet is affixed with three purple gems over the temples
  and forehead. This circlet has 3 charges and regains 1 charge at dusk each
  night. You may spend 1 charge and 2 AP to read the thoughts of one creature
  you can see within 200 ft of you for 1 minute. These thoughts are always
  surface level, and the target does not become aware their thoughts are being
  read.
</p>
<br />
<p>
  If you spend 1 minute concentrating on the circlet, taking 1d8 damage after
  this time, you may regain 1 charge. (1/Recoup)
</p>
<h3>
  <b>CLIMBER'S GLOVES</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Gloves, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  These sheepskin gloves have small metal protrusions on the tips of each
  finger. Gain a climb speed equal to your walking speed.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>CLOAK OF SHADOWS</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Cloak, Rare, Essence 20</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  This ragged linen cloak is dyed the deepest, darkest black. You gain +6 to
  DEX/Sneaking checks to remain hidden while in darkness. This cloak has 3
  charges and regains all spent charges at dusk. When you spend AP to move, you
  can expend a charge to step through a shadow and reappear in an unoccupied
  space in another shadow you can see within 90 ft of you.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>CRANE PAPER</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Supernatural Item, Common, Essence 10</em></p>
<br />

<br />
<p>
  These pages of thin silver-edged paper are of an expert quality. After
  whispering a target's name, the paper immediately folds into the shape of a
  bird and attempts to fly straight to the target's location. If the target is
  not on the same plane of existence as the Crane Paper when activated, the
  paper immediately combusts.
</p>
<h3>
  <b>DEPLOYABLE GLIDER</b>
</h3>
<p><em>Container, Uncommon, Essence 15</em></p>
<br />
<p>
  This leather pack is fixed over a metal harness that can be worn by a small or
  medium sized creature. While worn, it functions as a normal traveler's
  backpack or can be activated via a pull-string to deploy a pair of mechanical
  leather wings. For 10 minutes upon activation, you do not take falling damage,
  and for every 10 ft that you fall, you may move 10 ft horizontally. Once used,
  you must Take a Rest in order to reset this feature. (1/Rest)
</p>
